Canada plans an auction of three-yearbonds March 31 and an auction of seven-year bonds April 1, thefinance department said.    Further details would be announced March 25 on the bondsthat will be dated and delivered April 16, 1987.    The department said the issues are contingent upon finalParliamentary authority being given to Bill C-40, a previouslyannounced act to give the government supplementary borrowingauthority for fiscal 1987 (March 31) and borrowing authorityfor fiscal 1988. Reuter&#3;